WEBVTT



00:00:00.352 --> 00:00:07.168
Our scripture this morning comes to us from the book of 1 John 1:8-10.

00:00:07.008 --> 00:00:09.728
This might sound familiar to you all.

00:00:10.528 --> 00:00:15.584
But I invite you to hear the word of the Lord this morning anew.

00:00:15.488 --> 00:00:16.832
And freshly

00:00:19.200 --> 00:00:20.928
If we claim

00:00:21.056 --> 00:00:23.168
We don't have any sin.

00:00:24.160 --> 00:00:26.784
We deceive ourselves

00:00:26.944 --> 00:00:29.760
And the truth is not in us.

00:00:31.584 --> 00:00:32.512
But,

00:00:33.088 --> 00:00:36.320
If we confess our sin,

00:00:37.504 --> 00:00:40.800
He is faithful and just.

00:00:40.896 --> 00:00:42.880
To forgive our sins.

00:00:43.360 --> 00:00:47.296
And cleanse us from everything we've done wrong.

00:00:48.544 --> 00:00:50.080
If we claim

00:00:50.880 --> 00:00:52.544
we have never sinned.

00:00:53.888 --> 00:00:55.872
We make him a liar.

00:00:57.120 --> 00:00:59.392
And his word is not in us.

00:01:00.928 --> 00:01:04.256
This is the word of God for us, the people of God.

00:01:04.576 --> 00:01:06.336
Thanks be to God.

00:01:06.432 --> 00:01:07.520
Let us pray.

00:01:12.480 --> 00:01:14.720
Oh God have mercy on me a sinner

00:01:17.888 --> 00:01:20.416
Have mercy on us all.

00:01:24.768 --> 00:01:27.040
And let my unclean lips.

00:01:27.136 --> 00:01:30.496
Be made clean by the coal that you promised Isaiah.

00:01:31.904 --> 00:01:34.048
So that the words of my mouth

00:01:34.464 --> 00:01:37.376
And the meditations of all of our hearts.

00:01:37.984 --> 00:01:40.128
Might be acceptable in thy sight.

00:01:40.640 --> 00:01:41.760
Oh, Lord.

00:01:41.856 --> 00:01:42.944
Arbok.

00:01:42.688 --> 00:01:43.872
and are redeemed.

00:01:44.608 --> 00:01:45.504
Amen.

00:01:48.576 --> 00:01:51.264
Confession feels dangerous to me.

00:01:53.248 --> 00:01:55.520
Maybe it feels dangerous to you.

00:01:57.568 --> 00:02:01.792
and i think for me at least the reason why it feels dangerous.

00:02:02.208 --> 00:02:07.360
It's because over and over again, the church has proved itself to be

00:02:07.168 --> 00:02:11.616
To be an institution that cannot handle a confession.

00:02:13.312 --> 00:02:15.488
It's not a safe place.

00:02:15.200 --> 00:02:17.216
for confession to take place.

00:02:18.560 --> 00:02:24.672
The feeling of needing to move a sinful action of ours out into the light.

00:02:25.824 --> 00:02:28.832
So that there can be public accountability.

00:02:29.536 --> 00:02:32.160
Is terrifying to many.

00:02:33.504 --> 00:02:37.984
Because the church has used this information to cast judgment.

00:02:38.720 --> 00:02:40.256
And shun

00:02:40.672 --> 00:02:43.744
and reject our Christian siblings.

00:02:45.344 --> 00:02:49.856
I think we're also afraid of the consequences.

00:02:49.888 --> 00:02:51.168
For our sin.

00:02:54.592 --> 00:02:57.312
I know that we'd love to be able to

00:02:57.280 --> 00:03:00.096
Confess that we've done wrong and then

00:02:59.872 --> 00:03:02.624
Have that magically removed

00:03:02.912 --> 00:03:06.400
All the consequences of the things that we've done wrong.

00:03:07.744 --> 00:03:11.360
In our hearts, we know that's not how the world works.

00:03:12.256 --> 00:03:15.008
And so we hold on to our sins

00:03:15.520 --> 00:03:17.792
And then the burden

00:03:17.984 --> 00:03:19.872
Eats us alive

00:03:22.848 --> 00:03:25.280
All while maintaining an illusion.

00:03:25.856 --> 00:03:27.680
That we have it all together.

00:03:31.072 --> 00:03:33.888
That we're living our best lives now.

00:03:36.384 --> 00:03:39.744
Friends, that's not what God wants from us at all.

00:03:41.824 --> 00:03:45.120
Confession liberates us and others.

00:03:45.472 --> 00:03:49.376
It's not just from holding the things that weigh us down.

00:03:49.984 --> 00:03:54.144
Confessing allows Jesus to release us from the weight of

00:03:54.112 --> 00:03:56.640
Of keeping sin secret.

00:04:02.912 --> 00:04:04.256
From the weight of.

00:04:05.920 --> 00:04:07.328
Guilt itself.

00:04:09.824 --> 00:04:12.576
It's healthy for us to make confession.

00:04:12.384 --> 00:04:17.248
In good ways with people who we know will not hold this information.

00:04:17.056 --> 00:04:22.752
Against us we know how to keep that information secret between us and

00:04:22.848 --> 00:04:24.192
Thank God.

00:04:24.096 --> 00:04:25.056
And then

00:04:26.464 --> 00:04:29.728
There's a reason that many understand their pastors.

00:04:29.600 --> 00:04:33.056
as proper people to receive confession.

00:04:33.728 --> 00:04:43.776
As Foster says in his book Celebration of Disciplined Pastors, are very often folks who recognize the significance of Jesus' work on the cross.

00:04:43.296 --> 00:04:45.728
across and who know the reality of

00:04:45.824 --> 00:04:49.408
That every human being has sinned and fallen short

00:04:49.856 --> 00:04:51.328
and the glory of God.

00:04:54.176 --> 00:04:57.024
They also know that they are chief.

00:04:56.832 --> 00:04:58.400
Among the sinners.

00:04:59.232 --> 00:05:01.344
Just as Paul said himself.

00:05:03.936 --> 00:05:09.888
Pastors cannot burden shoulder the burden of confession alone.

00:05:11.008 --> 00:05:12.448
There's something,

00:05:12.448 --> 00:05:13.856
Very

00:05:13.824 --> 00:05:15.264
important.

00:05:15.264 --> 00:05:22.848
About having the kind of real relationships with your fellow Christian siblings, your fellow siblings in Christ.

00:05:24.320 --> 00:05:28.320
The kind of relationships that allow for real confession to happen.

00:05:30.048 --> 00:05:32.256
But the church has not done well.

00:05:32.448 --> 00:05:35.680
With stressing the corporate discipline.

00:05:36.000 --> 00:05:37.312
A confession.

00:05:41.056 --> 00:05:44.800
This group activity that should get us closer to God.

00:05:47.840 --> 00:05:53.632
And so we have become a people who not only do we not admit to each other,

00:05:53.920 --> 00:05:56.288
when we've done something wrong.

00:05:58.976 --> 00:06:05.888
But we also don't admit to the people who matter most in our lives and the places that matter most.

00:06:05.696 --> 00:06:07.168
In our lives.

00:06:08.800 --> 00:06:13.088
The places that need the witness of our confession the most.

00:06:13.888 --> 00:06:15.424
Our homes.

00:06:16.096 --> 00:06:17.472
At work.

00:06:18.176 --> 00:06:19.776
Our friendships

00:06:21.344 --> 00:06:22.400
Forget it.

00:06:22.176 --> 00:06:25.120
Admitting that we've done something wrong in those places.

00:06:25.376 --> 00:06:35.424
Instead, we have a certain brand of Christianity that has been given to us, that encourages us to double down when we know that we've done something wrong, because admitting that we.

00:06:34.944 --> 00:06:38.912
Something that we've done something wrong is a sign of weakness.

00:06:39.520 --> 00:06:42.240
It's a sign that you're a beta.

00:06:42.944 --> 00:06:44.576
That you're woke.

00:06:45.184 --> 00:06:49.856
That you're giving in to the pressure of a culture that won't let you be you.

00:06:52.576 --> 00:06:53.888
And instead,

00:06:53.856 --> 00:06:57.664
To seek the self-centeredness that we all think that we're

00:06:57.408 --> 00:06:59.168
Entitled to.

00:07:01.952 --> 00:07:07.488
Jesus is not in that attitude of self-sufficiency and isolationism.

00:07:08.608 --> 00:07:10.112
Jesus is not there.

00:07:10.976 --> 00:07:15.872
Hear the word of 1 John 1 again. If we claim we have never sinned,

00:07:15.712 --> 00:07:17.216
This is verse 10.

00:07:17.280 --> 00:07:21.952
We make him a liar and his word is not in us.

00:07:22.624 --> 00:07:28.928
The writer of 1 John, whoever that is, is not fooled by our aversion to accountability.

00:07:29.344 --> 00:07:31.904
And cuts right to the core.

00:07:32.640 --> 00:07:41.056
Of this honestly heretical understanding of individualized alpha male Christianity where might

00:07:40.800 --> 00:07:42.400
12 makes right.

00:07:44.000 --> 00:07:48.992
This is why so many in our country right now have an aversion to Jesus.

00:07:48.736 --> 00:07:50.976
